#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:107
msgid "In the following practices, we'll use conditions and improve the way our character's health changes so it has limits."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:107
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice title
msgid "Using Comparisons"
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:107
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid "Each [code]if[/code] statement below has a wrong comparison sign. Fix the comparison signs so every condition is [code]true[/code] and every [code]print()[/code] message runs."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:107
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid "Only change the comparison signs ([code]>[/code], [code]<[/code], [code]==[/code], [code]!=[/code]). Do not change the values or the messages."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:107
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid "Here are the four comparison signs and what they mean:"
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:107
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid ""
"[ul]\n"
"[code]>[/code]  Greater than\n"
"[code]<[/code]  Less than\n"
"[code]==[/code] Equal to\n"
"[code]!=[/code] Not equal to\n"
"[/ul]"
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:107
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid "For example, if [code]health[/code] is equal to [code]100[/code] and the message says \"health is greater than five,\" the correct comparison is [code]health > 5[/code], because 100 is greater than 5. That makes the condition evaluate to [code]true[/code] and print the message."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:107
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice description
msgid "Comparing values allows us to make decisions in code. But there's something wrong with these statements..."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:107
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice hint
msgid "Read each [code]print()[/code] message carefully. The message tells you what the comparison should mean. Then pick the sign that matches best."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:107
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice hint
msgid "Remember: you only need to change the [code]>[/code], [code]<[/code], [code]==[/code], or [code]!=[/code] symbols. Do not change numbers or the [code]print()[/code] calls!"
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:107
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice hint
msgid "For the last line, \"not equal to seven\" means you need the [code]!=[/code] sign: [code]health != 7[/code]."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:149
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice title
msgid "Limiting Healing"
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:149
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid "The [code]heal()[/code] function adds [code]amount[/code] to [code]health[/code]. But right now, health can increase forever, without limit! We want to stop it at [code]80[/code]."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:149
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid "I've defined a [code]health[/code] variable for you with a starting value of [code]20[/code]. Your task is to add a condition inside [code]heal()[/code] so that health is never greater than [code]80[/code]."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:149
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
#, fuzzy
msgid "To check your code, I will call the [code]heal()[/code] function twice, like this:"
msgstr "아래의 루프는 [code]cell[/code]을 세 번 변경할 것입니다."

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:149
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid ""
"[code]heal(40)[/code]\n"
"[code]heal(40)[/code]"
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:149
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid "After those two calls, [code]health[/code] should be equal to [code]80[/code]."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:149
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice description
msgid "As much as we might like, we don't want our robot to have too much health. Limit how much healing the robot can take."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:149
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice hint
msgid "The starting code already adds the amount to the [code]health[/code] variable: [code]health += amount[/code] is already there. You need to add a check [b]after[/b] it, otherwise the health will overshoot your limit."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:149
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice hint
msgid "Use [code]if health > 80:[/code] to detect when health went too high."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:149
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice hint
msgid "Inside that [code]if[/code] block, set health back to the limit: [code]health = 80[/code]. That's how you limit the value."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice title
msgid "Preventing Health from Going Below Zero"
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid "We want to display the health number on screen, like in many RPGs. But currently, the health can go below 0, which does not make sense. We want to stop at [code]0[/code]."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid "Complete the [code]take_damage()[/code] function so it does two things:"
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid ""
"1. Subtract [code]amount[/code] from [code]health[/code].\n"
"2. If [code]health[/code] is below [code]0[/code] after that, set it back to [code]0[/code]."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid "To check your code, I will call your [code]take_damage()[/code] function three times, like this:"
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid ""
"[code]take_damage(10)[/code]\n"
"[code]take_damage(10)[/code]\n"
"[code]take_damage(10)[/code]"
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice goal
msgid "After those three calls, [code]health[/code] should equal [code]0[/code], and not [code]-10[/code] or another value."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice description
msgid "Having a negative health value doesn't make a lot of sense. Make sure the robot's health can't go below zero."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice hint
msgid "Start by subtracting the damage: [code]health -= amount[/code]. This is how you apply damage."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice hint
msgid "To limit the health, after subtracting the amount, you need to add a condition and reset the health."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice hint
msgid "Here's how to write a condition to check if health went below zero: [code]if health < 0:[/code]."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-13-conditions/lesson.bbcode:178
#. TRANSLATORS: Practice hint
msgid "Inside the [code]if[/code] block, you can reset the health like this: [code]health = 0[/code]."
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-14-multiplying/lesson.bbcode:1
#. TRANSLATORS: Lesson header
msgid "Multiplying"
msgstr ""

#: course/lesson-14-multiplying/lesson.bbcode:9
msgid "We define a [code]level[/code] variable to keep track of the level of the robot. It starts at level one."
msgstr "우리는 로봇의 레벨을 추적하기 위해 [code]level[/code] 변수를 정의합니다. 이 변수는 처음에 레벨 1에서 시작합니다."

